1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:08,250
They tortured us with psychological warfare by saying, tomorrow you will
be executed, in a week you will be executed, you will not leave here

2
00:00:08,583 --> 00:00:12,000
They wanted you to live in an
atmosphere as close to death as possible

3
00:00:14,250 --> 00:00:22,833
The guard opens the small hatch on you and says, get ready, pray,
and make your supplications, you will be executed in two days

4
00:00:23,416 --> 00:00:28,333
You wait for those two days to
pass, wishing they would never end

5
00:00:28,833 --> 00:00:32,625
Because after that you will die,
and you have believed every word

6
00:00:33,750 --> 00:00:36,500
Interviewer: Did they show
you their propaganda videos?

7
00:00:36,625 --> 00:00:43,041
They did not show anything, no videos or anything else.
We were in solitary cells, we could not see anything

8
00:00:44,291 --> 00:00:49,875
Interviewer: They had a newspaper called
<i>al-Naba</i>. Did they distribute it to you in prison?

9
00:00:51,000 --> 00:01:00,291
As for things they brought us, they only brought food.
They never distributed a newspaper or showed a video at all

10
00:01:02,291 --> 00:01:05,375
Interviewer: How do you feel
standing in this place now?

11
00:01:06,125 --> 00:01:14,416
My feelings are very difficult. Standing
in this place where I was imprisoned

12
00:01:14,750 --> 00:01:20,250
Is harder than the mind can imagine. I saw
things I will never forget as long as I live

